{"_id":"BardolfGreed","name":"Bardolf Greed - The Wealthy Industrialist","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-noble-grey.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a profit for me","My body is old, but my mind remains infallible"],"agenda":"Own every business and aspect of trade in Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control","gifts":[{"name":"Smell the Deal","description":"Bardolf is a master of negotiation and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf can obtain one of the following pieces of information: 1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent Bardolf from using this Gift on them."}],"background":"A wealthy industrialist in his seventies who made his fortune through shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf decided to dedicate his life to money. He moved to Whitehaven, an unremarkable town whose only resource was rich mines beneath the city. Within years, he transformed it into an industrial city by trapping all inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. He seized property, leveled houses to build factories and dormitories, and forced the Browne brothers (who cared for the community) out on the street. His greed and exploitation led to a mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine, and now a gang called the Pig Heads wages war against him. His face is plump with thick lupine sideburns, shrewd eyes peek over small round glasses, and he never feels safe despite his personal guards."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"victim-antagonist","status":"quest-giver"}}
{"_id":"EdwardChief","name":"Edward - The Miners' Chief","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-ochre.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn his death","Everyone in the mine does what I say","I hate foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work","I allow Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died"],"background":"The chief of the miners at Whitehaven's coal mine, an honest and dutiful man who ensures the mine works at full capacity under watchful control. Edward is a long-time friend of Arthur Browne and mourns his death in the mine collapse. Everyone in the mine follows his orders without question. He hates foreigners who want to poke their noses into his work, protecting the mine's operations for Bardolf Greed. Out of respect for their friendship and grief, Edward allows Frank Browne into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur supposedly died. What Edward doesn't know is that Arthur is still alive beneath the mine, and Frank uses these visits to bring supplies and communicate with his brother through the hidden well leading to the cave where The God Under the Mine's head emerges from the rock."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"mine-overseer","knowledge":"unknowingly-aiding-brownes"}}
{"_id":"EmmaFriend","name":"Emma - The Childhood Friend","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-pink.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a childhood friend of Clarence","I have a special relationship with him","He has always promised that he will take me away from this place","But I know that he will never abandon his brothers","I understand that he has a big secret, but he tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark"],"background":"A childhood friend of Clarence Browne with whom she has a special relationship. Clarence has always promised that he will take her away from Whitehaven, but Emma knows deep down that he will never abandon his brothers. She understands that Clarence has a big secret - she suspects his involvement with the Pig Heads - but he tries to protect her by keeping her in the dark about the revolution. Emma offers her services in the city and is curious to talk to foreigners, possibly seeking news or hoping for a way out of the industrial town that has become a battleground between Bardolf Greed and the Browne brothers."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"innocent-informant","relationship":"clarences-love-interest"}}
{"_id":"GreedGuards","name":"Greed's Guards","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-worn-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["We are long-time mercenaries","Paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty"],"background":"About a dozen men from Bardolf Greed's personal guard who stand with their backs to the wall in his mansion, staring at guests like silent statues. They are long-time mercenaries paid handsomely for their loyalty, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist does not feel safe despite his power and wealth. They protect Bardolf during meetings and ensure his orders are carried out throughout Whitehaven."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"guards","usage":"use-multiple-dozen"}}
{"_id":"MarthaBrowne","name":"Martha Browne - The Mother","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/elder-female-gray.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am the mother of three brothers","I am so old that I have almost completely lost my sight","My son Frank takes care of me, but he doesn't tell me anything","I am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a mother tells me so"],"background":"The elderly mother of Clarence, Frank, and Arthur Browne. She is so old that she has almost completely lost her sight. Her son Frank takes care of her, but he doesn't tell her anything about their plans or the Pig Heads revolution. Despite everyone telling her that Arthur died in the mine collapse, Martha is convinced that he is not dead - her instinct as a mother tells her so, and she is right. Arthur is alive, trapped beneath the mine, feeding on the flesh of The God Under the Mine and orchestrating the gang's war against Bardolf Greed."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"innocent-mother","knowledge":"unaware-of-truth"}}
{"_id":"PigHeads","name":"The Pig Heads","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-pig-tan.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["We are a band of revolutionaries in the service of the three brothers","The God's flesh gives us power and fills us with the anger we need to wage our war"],"gifts":[{"name":"Pigs' Gang","description":"When they act, each member of the gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random power, roll 1 die:\n\n1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional Wound once per Scene\n2. Speed, once per Scene acts 2 times consecutively\n3. Resistance, +1 Wound\n4. Abomination, +1 to Opposition Level\n5. Grunt, once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it receive 1 Penalty on their next action\n6. Out of control, the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood."}],"background":"A criminal gang that wanders through the backways of Whitehaven. They kidnap or injure only factory workers to make them unable to work, wearing grotesque pig masks to hide their faces. Nobody recognizes them because of the masks. In reality, they are miners who have eaten meat contaminated with the flesh of The God Under the Mine, distributed secretly by Frank Browne at the slaughterhouse. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence Browne approaches them, offering the opportunity to join the gang in their personal war against Bardolf Greed. With over fifty Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the days before he can launch his personal revolution. The God's flesh gives them the power to transform, their heads becoming those of pigs with various enhanced abilities."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"gang-members","usage":"use-multiple-fifty-plus"}}
{"_id":"WilliamLawyer","name":"William - The Man of Law","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of Bardolf's secrets","I manage the accounts of both the Factories and mine with zealous attention"],"background":"Bardolf Greed's trusted lawyer who manages all accounts for the factories and mine. He records everything in a large black leather book and stands behind Bardolf during meetings. William knows all of Greed's secrets and handles the legal maneuvering that allows the industrialist to maintain control over Whitehaven."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"greed-lieutenant"}}